HEADWORD: Ixodidae
<hw>Ixodidae</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A natural family of ticks
having a hard shield on the back and mouth parts that project from the
head; the hard ticks.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Ixodidae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
